---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { base } from '@/lib/url';
---
<BaseLayout title="Contribute a skill">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-10 prose-devops">
    <h1>Contribute a skill</h1>
    <p>
      A skill is a self-contained folder in <code>catalog/&lt;slug&gt;/</code>. Every skill ships as a single portable <code>SKILL.md</code> per the <a href="https://agentskills.io/" rel="noopener">Agent Skills open standard</a> — loaded natively by GitHub Copilot (VS Code, CLI, Cloud Agent), Claude, and any compatible client — plus a trainer note so instructors get a lesson plan for free.
    </p>
    <h2>The 30-second path</h2>
    <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/petender/ms-devops-agent-skills
cd ms-devops-agent-skills
npm install
npm run new-skill -- --slug my-awesome-skill --name "My Awesome Skill" --category ci
npm run validate
npm run dev</code></pre>
    <p>Open a PR — CI validates the schema and runs a full build.</p>
    <h2>Catalog entry shape</h2>
    <pre><code>catalog/&lt;slug&gt;/
├── metadata.json           # catalog entry
├── SKILL.md                # single portable skill (name + description frontmatter)
├── trainer.md              # optional lesson plan
├── assets/                 # optional templates / sample files
└── scripts/                # optional helper scripts</code></pre>
    <p>See <a href="https://github.com/petender/ms-devops-agent-skills/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a> for the full guide, and <a href={`${base}`}>the catalog</a> for examples.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
